E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20deal%20with%20Paul%20Weiss%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20his%20war%20on%20Big%20Law.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20firms%20fighting%20Trump's%20orders%20have%20used%20the%20deal%20as%20evidence%20that%20they're%20legally%20flimsy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20lawyer%20for%20Susman%20Godfrey%20argued%20that%20it%20proves%20the%20orders%20were%20never%20about%20national%20security.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-trump-executive-order-agreement-language-dei-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20deal%20with%20Paul%20Weiss%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20his%20first%20big%20win%20in%20his%20war%20against%20Big%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20it's%20coming%20back%20to%20haunt%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-big-law-fight-firms-legal-dilemma-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20law%20firms%20choosing%20to%20fight%3C%2Fa%3E%20Trump's%20executive%20orders%20targeting%20them%2C%20rather%20than%20striking%20deals%20with%20the%20president%2C%20the%20Paul%20Weiss%20deal%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20potent%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20cited%20Trump's%20quick%20revocation%20of%20the%20order%20%E2%80%94%20just%20six%20days%20after%20it%20was%20initially%20issued%20%E2%80%94%20to%20argue%20that%20they%20never%20had%20any%20legitimacy%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20The%20order%2C%20had%20it%20been%20carried%20out%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-memo-orders-big-law-firms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20have%20revoked%20the%20security%20clearances%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Paul%20Weiss%20lawyers%20out%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20national%20interest%26quot%3B%20and%20barred%20them%20from%20entering%20government-owned%20buildings%2C%20potentially%20including%20even%20courthouses%20and%20post%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20emerged%20again%20in%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20federal%20courtroom%20on%20Thursday%20afternoon%20as%20a%20lawyer%20representing%20the%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-big-law-executive-orders-decisions-damage-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESusman%20Godfrey%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20a%20federal%20judge%20that%20Trump's%20turnabout%20on%20the%20Paul%20Weiss%20order%20was%20evidence%20that%20the%20White%20House%20never%20really%20believed%20the%20law%20firms%20posed%20a%20national%20security%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20change%20in%20circumstances%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20trustworthiness%20of%20Paul%20Weiss%20between%20the%20issuing%20of%20that%20executive%20order%20and%20its%20rescission%20a%20few%20days%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Donald%20B.%20Verrilli%2C%20Jr.%2C%20a%20lawyer%20at%20Munger%20Tolles%20representing%20Susman%20Godfrey.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20in%20some%20ways%20that%20tells%20you%20all%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20whether%20there's%20anything%20legitimate%20about%20the%20suspension.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-trump-executive-order-agreement-language-dei-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaul%20Weiss%20agreed%20to%20a%20deal%20with%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20March%2C%20its%20chairman%2C%20Brad%20Karp%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-brad-karp-email-staff-trump-deal-executive-order-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20lawyers%20at%20the%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20agreement%20resolved%20an%20%26quot%3Bexistential%20crisis%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Bcould%20easily%20have%20destroyed%20our%20firm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-big-law-executive-orders-disarm-legal-opponents-pro-bono-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edivided%20the%20legal%20profession%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Critics%20said%20that%20by%20choosing%20to%20reach%20an%20agreement%20with%20Trump%20instead%20of%20fight%20in%20court%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Perkins%20Coie%20had%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20Paul%20Weiss%20empowered%20Trump%20to%20go%20after%20more%20Big%20Law%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEight%20more%20Big%20Law%20firms%20made%20deals%20with%20Trump%2C%20averting%20altogether%20possible%20executive%20orders%20targeting%20them%2C%20and%20pledging%20a%20total%20of%20nearly%20%241%20billion%20in%20pro%20bono%20hours%20toward%20Trump's%20political%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20four%20law%20firms%20fighting%20executive%20orders%20%E2%80%94%20Perkins%20Coie%2C%20Jenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%2C%20WilmerHale%2C%20and%20Susman%20Godfrey%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Paul%20Weiss%20deal%20had%20the%20opposite%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20clear%20indication%2C%20they%20have%20all%20argued%2C%20that%20the%20legal%20justifications%20for%20Trump's%20orders%20were%20baloney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20legal%20precedents%2C%20government%20agencies%20are%20required%20to%20conduct%20an%20%26quot%3Bindividualized%20review%26quot%3B%20to%20issue%20and%20revoke%20security%20clearances%2C%20judges%20have%20ruled%20in%20the%20cases.%20Reversing%20the%20Paul%20Weiss%20order%20in%20under%20a%20week%20was%20clearly%20too%20short%20a%20time%20to%20individually%20weigh%20whether%20each%20person%20working%20at%20the%20firm%20posed%20an%20actual%20national%20security%20threat%2C%20the%20four%20law%20firms%20have%20each%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThursday's%20court%20hearing%2C%20overseen%20by%20US%20District%20Judge%20Loren%20AliKhan%2C%20was%20over%20whether%20the%20judge%20should%20permanently%20block%20the%20order%20targeting%20Susman%20Godfrey%2C%20a%20law%20firm%20that%20represents%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20in%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20has%20represented%20Dominion%20Voting%20S