Meta%20is%20actively%20trying%20to%20cut%20into.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20overall%20investment%2C%20Mosseri%20said%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-spent-hundreds-of-millions-dollars-creators-ftc-adam-mosseri-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMeta%20has%20spent%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20millions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20maybe%20a%20billion%20or%20two%26quot%3B%20during%20his%20time%20at%20the%20company%20supporting%20the%20wider%20creative%20ecosystem.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20touches%20everything%20from%20incentive%20payments%20to%20the%20physical%20infrastructure%20necessary%20to%20power%20Instagram's%20AI-backed%20recommendations.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20just%20seeing%20more%20and%20more%20power%20shift%20from%20institutions%20to%20individuals%20across%20the%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosseri%20testified.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216139b4b-71c7-4e3d-a8ef-86fa47842d6a%5C%22%3EInstagram's%20struggles%20around%20content%20safety%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESusan%20Musser%2C%20the%20FTC%20attorney%20who%20led%20Mosseri's%20questioning%2C%20repeatedly%20questioned%20the%20Instagram%20head%20over%20his%20initial%20concerns%20about%20how%20the%20app%20was%20ensuring%20the%20safety%20of%20its%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMosser%20pointed%20to%20an%20email%20from%20October%2019%2C%202018%2C%20less%20than%20a%20month%20after%20Mosseri%20became%20head%20of%20the%20app%2C%20in%20which%20he%20said%20that%20Facebook%20was%20not%20investing%20enough%20in%20Instagram's%20Well-being%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20underinvested%20in%20Well-being%20and%20were%2C%20until%20recently%2C%20the%20resources%20we%20do%20have%20are%20underleveraged%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosseri%20wrote%20to%20someone%20whose%20full%20name%20was%20redacted.%20The%20initial%20email%20the%20person%20wrote%20was%20titled%2C%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20prioritize%20integrity%20efforts%20over%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20we%20must%20fight%20fakes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20internal%20Facebook%20document%20also%20showed%20that%20Instagram%20had%20significantly%20fewer%20engineers%20devoted%20to%20well-being%20than%20the%20main%20app.%20According%20to%20the%202018%20summary%2C%20Instagram%20had%2040%20engineers%20dedicated%20to%20doing%20such%20work.%20Facebook%20had%20900.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20lawyer%20Aaron%20Panner%20later%20asked%20Mosseri%20if%20Meta%20employees%20typically%20received%20everything%20they%20requested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNever%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosseri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-head-adam-mosseri-testifies-in-meta-ftc-antitrust-trial-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746739375000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681cb4c0a466d2b74ab55f34%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-head-adam-mosseri-testifies-in-meta-ftc-antitrust-trial-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Head%20of%20Instagram%20Adam%20Mosseri%20testified%20Thursday%20in%20the%20Meta%20antitrust%20trial%20in%20DC%20federal%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths%2CNatalie%20Musumeci%2CPranav%20Dixit%2CSydney%20Bradley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-head-adam-mosseri-testifies-in-meta-ftc-antitrust-trial-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Labor%20judge%20says%20Costco's%20confidentiality%20agreement%20for%20handling%20employee%20complaints%20is%20unlawful%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Costco%20warehouse%20seen%20at%20dusk.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67992daeeb4be2fff9a29444%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECostco's%20lawyer%20argued%20that%20confidentiality%20rules%20are%20intended%20to%20protect%20the%20integrity%20of%20investigations%20and%20are%20in%20the%20shared%20interest%20of%20the%20company%20and%20workers.%3Cp%3EDominick%20Reuter%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20US%20labor%20judge%20has%20decided%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-first-store-opened-vintage-photos-2019-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECostco%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20matter%20involving%20worker%20confidentiality%20agreements.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20case%20involves%20a%20worker%20who%20had%20to%20agree%20not%20to%20discuss%20an%20internal%20sexual%20harassment%20investigation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20NLRB%20argued%20that%20Costco's%20policy%20%26quot%3Bappears%20to%20instead%20protect%20the%20harasser.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-shareholders-reject-anti-dei-proposal-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECostco's%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20surrounding%20internal%20investigations%20are%20under%20scrutiny%20for%20being%20%26quot%3Boverly%20broad%26quot%3B%20and%20in%20violation%20of%20employees'%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20US%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20judge%20Andrew%20Gollin%20decided%20against%20Costco%20in%20a%20matter%20involving%20the%20confidentiality%20agreements%20that%20workers%20are%20expected%20to%20sign%20when%20raising%20issues%20with%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20specific%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fcase%2F10-CA-316194%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20brought%20on%20behalf%20of%20Jessica%20Georg%2C%20who%20in%202022%20used%20Costco's%20%26quot%3BOpen%20Door%26quot%3B%20policy%20to%20file%20an%20internal%20complaint%20that%20she%20was%20sexually%20harassed%20by%20a%20co-worker%2C%20according%20to%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20process%2C%20Georg%20was%20required%20to%20sign%20a%20confidentiality%20agreement%20that%20barred%20her%20from%20discussing%20the%20open%20matter%20with%20coworkers.%20She%20later%20received%20a%20letter%20from%20Costco%20that%20said%20the%20employee%20was%20fired%2C%20the%20case%20was%20closed%2C%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20hope%20and%20expect%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20information%20would%20continue%20to%20remain%20confidential%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaccording%20to%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NLRB%20and%20Georg%20each%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story%2C%20and%20neither%20Costco%20nor%20its%20attorney%20responded%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20briefing%2C%20Costco's%20lawyer%20Paul%20Galligan%20argued%20that%20the%20confidentiality%20rules%20are%20intended%20to%20protect%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20investigation%20and%20are%20in%20the%20shared%20interest%20of%20the%20company%20and%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20employees%20to%20be%20candid%20in%20their%20statements%20knowing%20that%20their%20statements%20will%20be%20treated%20confidentiality.%20It%20is%20probably%20more%20critical%20in%20an%20industry%20like%20retail%20where%20employees%20work%20closely%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Galligan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20in%20the%20briefing%20the%20rules%20aren't%20intended%20to%20dissuade%20employees%20from%20discussing%20things%20like%20wages%2C%20working%20conditions%2C%20or%20forming%20a%20union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Costco's%20investigation%20found%20that%20the%20individual%20about%20whom%20Georg%20complained%20also%20had%20several%20prior%20complaints%20filed%20against%20him%2C%20and%20Georg%20later%20testified%20she%20felt%20she%20or%20her%20coworkers%20with%20similar%20experiences%20felt%20they%20might%20be%20risking%20their%20jobs%20if%20they%20shared%20information%20about%20alleged%20patterns%20of%20behavior%20by%20an%20individual%20employee%20about%20whom%20they%20had%20raised%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20tailored%20confidentiality%20agreement%20could%20still%20protect%20sensitive%20information%20while%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-strike-authorization-union-teamsters-workers-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassuring%20workers%20of%20their%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protect%20themselves%20against%20harassment%2C%20the%20NLRB%20attorneys%20said%20in%20a%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NLRB%20attorneys%20argued%20that%20Costco's%20policy%20%26quot%3Bappears%20to%20instead%20protect%20the%20harasser%20who%20has%20had%20individual%20complaints%20dismissed%20over%20and%20over%2C%20because%20no%20one%20outside%20the%20investigator%20is%20privy%20to%20the%20serial%20nature%20of%20the%20harassment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECostco's%20lawyer%20argued%20that%20the%20company's%20employee%20handbook%20explains%20that%20the%20confidentiality%20requirement%20is%20not%20intended%20to%20discourage%20workers%20from%20exercising%20their%20rights.%20The%20NLRB%20argued%2C%20and%20the%20judge%20agreed%2C%20that%20having%20workers%20sign%20a%20separate%20form%20(as%20was%20the%20case%20here)%20could%20reasonably%20cause%20confusion%20for%20a%20typical%20worker%20and%20lead%20them%20to%20fear%20for%20their%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Judge%20Gollin's%20proposed%20remedy%20is%20that%20Costco%20post%20a%20notice%20in%20the%20one%20warehouse%20where%20the%20violation%20occurred%2C%20since%20the%20NLRB%20did%20not%20prove%20conclusively%20that%20similar%20confidentiality%20forms%20were%20used%20at%20all%20of%20the%20company's%20US%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20now%20heads%20to%20the%20NLRB's%20board%2C%20with%20exceptions%20to%20the%20decision%20due%20by%20June%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGot%20a%20tip%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adreuter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmail%20Dominick%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20call%2Ftext%2FSignal%20at%20646.768.4750.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-confidentiality-agreement-worker-complaints-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746738995000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67992daeeb4be2fff9a29444%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-confidentiality-agreement-worker-complaints-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20US%20labor%20judge%20decided%20Costco's%20rules%20barring%20workers%20from%20discussing%20harassment%20investigations%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20rights%2C%20which%20Costco%20has%20denied.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dreuter%40businessinsider.com%20(Dominick%20Reuter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-confidentiality-agreement-worker-complaints-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20keeps%2010%25%20baseline%20tariff%2C%20eases%20auto%20and%20metal%20duties%20in%20trade%20deal%20with%20UK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746738895000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-121009522%2Cimgsize-13288.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-keeps-10-baseline-tariff-eases-auto-and-metal-duties-in-trade-deal-with-uk%2Farticleshow%2F121009515.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F121009515.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20President%20Trump%20confirmed%20a%20new%20trade%20framework%20w