e%20connection%20Charlie%20has%20with%20the%20killer%20or%20the%20person%20killed%20%E2%80%94%20that%20ends%20up%20being%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20of%20the%20writing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Natasha%20Lyonne%20surrounded%20by%20Cynthia%20Erivos%20looking%20over%20a%20cliff%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681b5d89c6ad288d14803e44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENatasha%20Lyonne%20and%20several%20Cynthia%20Erivos%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BPoker%20Face%26quot%3B%20season%202.%3Cp%3EPeacock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20perfect%20example%20is%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20season%20two%2C%20which%20you%20directed.%20In%20it%2C%20Charlie%20meets%20Cynthia%20Erivo's%20character%20while%20working%20at%20an%20apple%20orchard.%20Was%20that%20something%20not%20used%20in%20the%20last%20season%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20the%20orchard%20setting%20was%20fresh.%20I%20think%20part%20of%20it%20came%20from%20we%20were%20shooting%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20we%20were%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20around%20there%3F%20Oh%2C%20an%20apple%20orchard.%20That%20will%20be%20ideal!%26quot%3B%20But%20that's%20also%20a%20fun%20element%20of%20it.%20It%20harkens%20back%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BColumbo%26quot%3B%20thing%20or%20more%20%26quot%3BQuantum%20Leap%2C%26quot%3B%20every%20episode%20zooming%20into%20a%20microcosm%20fishbowl%20of%20a%20world.%20Episode%201%20came%20from%20the%20notion%20of%20all%20these%20false%20starts.%20We%20could%20have%20had%20a%20%26quot%3BPoker%20Face%26quot%3B%20episode%20set%20in%20a%20haunted%20house%20hayride%20or%20a%20parking%20garage%2C%20but%20those%20pesky%20gunmen%20keep%20chasing%20Charlie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20you%20personally%20involved%20in%20selecting%20the%20guest%20stars%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah.%20The%20casting%20process%20for%20the%20main%20guest%20stars%20is%20a%20text%20thread%20with%20me%2C%20Natasha%2C%20Tony%20Tost%2C%20the%20showrunner%2C%20and%20our%20casting%20directors.%20Sometimes%20it's%20just%20me%20and%20Natasha%20bouncing%20back%20and%20forth%20ideas%20of%20friends%20that%20we%20want%20to%20text.%20So%20it's%20a%20very%20fun%2C%20personal%2C%20and%20chaotic%20process%20because%20we're%20casting%20the%20show%20week%20to%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20figuring%20out%20if%20schedules%20are%20going%20to%20fit.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20also%20an%20element%20that's%20also%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20out%20the%20other%20night%20at%20dinner%20and%20I%20ran%20into%20so%20and%20so.%20Do%20you%20think%20they'd%20want%20to%20be%20in%20this%20episode%20that%20starts%20shooting%20on%20Monday%3F%26quot%3B%20There's%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20fly-by-the-seat-of-your-pants%20element%20to%20it%2C%20which%20is%20fun%20and%20terrifying.%20It's%20amazing%20to%20get%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20season%20after%20that%20process%20and%20look%20back%20and%20see%20the%20roster%20that%20we've%20gotten.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20an%20actor%20you've%20gone%20out%20to%20for%20the%20show%20ever%20declined%20because%20they're%20holding%20out%20for%20a%20role%20in%20a%20%26quot%3BKnives%20Out%26quot%3B%20movie%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%5B%3Cem%3ELaughs%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20Not%20to%20my%20knowledge.%20If%20that%20has%20happened%2C%20they%20have%20not%20given%20that%20reason%20to%20me.%20But%20also%20being%20in%20one%20doesn't%20preclude%20you%20from%20being%20in%20the%20other.%20And%20these%20are%20very%20different%20processes%20casting%20both.%20We%20cast%20as%20we're%20shooting%20with%20%26quot%3BPoker%20Face.%26quot%3B%20And%20we%20started%20shooting%20that%20halfway%20into%20the%20%26quot%3BWake%20Up%20Dead%20Man%26quot%3B%20shoot.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20f